        <p>Instant messaging is a form of real-time communication between two or more people based on typed text. Windows Live Messenger (formerly known as MSN Messenger, and often referred to as MSN) is available in more than 60 countries and in 26 languages (MSN Internal Data, June 2006). It allows its users to make friends with people they find attractive and likeable. The photographs provided by the users accompany personal information such as age, family status, hobbies, etc.</p>
